description: Damara Gold Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in Canada. The company primarily explores for gold. It acquires a 75% interest in the Placer Mountain property that includes 22 mineral claims covering an area of approximately 8,955 hectares located to the south of Princeton, British Columbia. The company was formerly known as Solomon Resources Limited and changed its name to Damara Gold Corp. in September 2014. Damara Gold Corp. was incorporated in 1989 and is headquartered in Kelowna, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Lawrence J. Nagy B.A., B.A. Geology
